data.content:
Three things break. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — no longer takes an expression tree

The parameter changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`. Your manual expression tree code **won't compile**. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` gymnastics needed.

---

### 2. Complex type columns — two changes

**a) Duplicate column names are now auto-uniquified.** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously silently shared one column; now they get distinct names (e.g. `Street`, `Street1`). To preserve the old behavior, pin names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path in column names.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was mapped to `BillingAddress_City`; now it becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To keep the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

⚠️ Both changes affect existing migrations — a new migration will try to rename columns. Either pin names with `HasColumnName` or generate and apply a migration.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (supports redaction of inlined constants). Add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
